<%- include('../partials/tw-head') -%>
<body class="flex min-h-full flex-col bg-slate-50 text-slate-800 antialiased">
<%- include('../partials/tw-header') -%>
<main class="flex-1">
  <section class="bg-navy py-14 text-white sm:py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
        <span class="rounded-full bg-white/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-amber-200"><%= SITE.availability.badge %></span>
        <span class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-200/80"><%= PRODUCTS.eden.tag %></span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl"><%= PRODUCTS.eden.headline %></h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-200 leading-relaxed"><%= PRODUCTS.eden.subhead %></p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="compare.html" class="inline-flex rounded-lg bg-faithGold px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-amber-600 focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-amber-300 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-navy">Compare products</a>
        <a href="products.html" class="inline-flex rounded-lg border border-white/25 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-white/10">All products</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">Research software—not a mode inside finance</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Eden is its own product: a local-first system for aggregating, analyzing, prioritizing, and evaluating sources. It is not a feature tucked inside CFO or Ledger.</p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Material is organized into claims, facts, and context. Summaries remain tied to sources, with structured outputs you can audit.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="border-y border-slate-200 bg-white py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold text-navy">What Eden ingests</h2>
      <ul class="mt-8 space-y-3 text-slate-600">
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-faithGold"></span>Screen recordings</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-faithGold"></span>Video—local files or public platforms such as YouTube, Rumble, Vimeo, or Instagram</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-faithGold"></span>Articles, documents, images, and screenshots</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-faithGold"></span>Your own files alongside sources you choose</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-8 text-center text-sm text-slate-500">Eden transcribes audio, runs OCR where needed, and produces structured research with citations.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy"><%= SITE.steward.name %> prioritizes what matters to you</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Steward is logic-driven, not open-ended generation. In Eden it helps prioritize facts using <em>your</em> context—so the same material can be ordered differently for different questions.</p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Sources are weighed for consistency, evidence, cross-source agreement, and relevance. Eden clarifies the landscape; it does not replace your judgment.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">What Eden is not</h2>
    <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-slate-600">
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-faithGold">—</span>It does not write papers or replace authorship.</li>
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-faithGold">—</span>It does not pass judgment on people.</li>
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-faithGold">—</span>It does not bypass paywalls or harvest restricted content.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-navy py-14 text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 text-center sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Related products, separate missions</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-slate-200 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white">CFO</strong> is the financial operating system. <strong class="text-white">Ledger</strong> is the identity vault and document layer. Eden answers a different question: turning diverse sources into prioritized, citable research—on your machine.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
        <a href="product-cfo.html" class="rounded-lg border border-white/25 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-white/10">CFO</a>
        <a href="product-ledger.html" class="rounded-lg border border-white/25 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-white/10">Ledger</a>
        <a href="compare.html" class="rounded-lg bg-faithGold px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-navy hover:bg-amber-500">Compare all</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('../partials/tw-availability') %>
</main>
<%- include('../partials/tw-footer') %>
<%- include('../partials/tw-scripts') %>
</body>
</html>
